1
00:01:09,305 --> 00:01:10,344
Hey! Stop!

2
00:01:18,785 --> 00:01:22,065
Where are you running off to? You mother…

3
00:01:22,785 --> 00:01:26,225
Leave me! Leave me, woman!

4
00:01:26,745 --> 00:01:27,585
Hey! Stop!

5
00:01:29,225 --> 00:01:31,465
Stop!

6
00:01:38,905 --> 00:01:39,825
Stop!

7
00:01:41,025 --> 00:01:42,265
I will kill you if you don't move.

8
00:01:42,345 --> 00:01:43,345
Move ! Move it!

9
00:01:45,745 --> 00:01:47,385
Move! Let's go. Let's go.

10
00:02:00,665 --> 00:02:01,705
Water?

11
00:02:02,785 --> 00:02:04,145
Madam, have some water.

12
00:02:05,105 --> 00:02:07,865
Hey, you ran so much.
Why don't you want water, Swati?

13
00:02:15,905 --> 00:02:18,425
Your system will get upset. Come on.

14
00:02:19,745 --> 00:02:21,025
Is your belly full?

15
00:02:27,185 --> 00:02:29,865
Arjun Meena, so this is all your doing?

16
00:02:31,065 --> 00:02:35,145
Hey, let go of my hand. Hey. Let go!

17
00:02:41,425 --> 00:02:44,385
<i>Ramesh bhai, if you want the girl,</i>
<i>you have to pay 50 lakhs.</i>

18
00:02:44,465 --> 00:02:47,465
<i>Send someone to the helipad.</i>
<i>I'll be there in an hour.</i>

19
00:03:08,665 --> 00:03:11,985
Hold on a little longer.
Then you can relax all you want.

20
00:03:16,225 --> 00:03:18,305
<i>My name is Arjun Meena.</i>

21
00:03:18,825 --> 00:03:23,065
<i>I work as a Superintendent in Customs.</i>
<i>But I'm under suspension right now.</i>

22
00:03:23,145 --> 00:03:26,905
<i>There's a long story behind my suspension.</i>

23
00:03:26,985 --> 00:03:31,425
<i>I'll tell you about it some other time.</i>
<i>For now, let's start from the beginning.</i>

24
00:03:33,465 --> 00:03:36,145
{\an8}<i>Spread over 2,000 acres,</i>
<i>Mumbai International Airport</i>

25
00:03:37,265 --> 00:03:39,665
{\an8}<i>is one of the busiest airports</i>
<i>of the world.</i>

26
00:04:08,585 --> 00:04:10,945
<i>This airport which handles</i>
<i>over 1,000 flights</i>

27
00:04:11,025 --> 00:04:15,385
<i>and over 150,000 passengers daily,</i>

28
00:04:15,465 --> 00:04:17,945
<i>also gets 30,000 tons of cargo every year.</i>

29
00:04:18,985 --> 00:04:23,225
<i>For centuries, the places at the center of</i>
<i>travel and business also faced</i> taskaree.

30
00:04:23,825 --> 00:04:26,064
Taskaree<i>… which means smuggling.</i>

31
00:04:37,705 --> 00:04:41,465
<i>If you buy any item</i>
<i>over 50,000 from a foreign country,</i>

32
00:04:41,545 --> 00:04:43,825
<i>you have to pay a duty on that item.</i>

33
00:04:43,905 --> 00:04:46,345
<i>How many pay this duty?</i>
<i>Let's not dwell on it.</i>

34
00:04:47,745 --> 00:04:50,225
<i>But the simple definition of</i> taskaree <i>is</i>

35
00:04:50,305 --> 00:04:54,025
<i>bringing anything illegally</i>
<i>into the country.</i>

36
00:04:54,105 --> 00:04:55,825
<i>Anything from gold to betel nut.</i>

37
00:04:57,185 --> 00:05:01,425
<i>These</i> taskars, <i>meaning smugglers,</i>
<i>smuggle everything</i>

38
00:05:01,505 --> 00:05:03,425
<i>that fetches them profit.</i>

39
00:05:05,625 --> 00:05:09,705
<i>But before pocketing the profit,</i>
<i>these smugglers have to browbeat us.</i>

40
00:05:10,225 --> 00:05:14,425
{\an8}<i>Who are we? We are the worst nightmare</i>
<i>for the smugglers of the world.</i>

41
00:05:14,505 --> 00:05:18,105
{\an8}Seema Shulk <i>Adhikari,</i>
<i>meaning Customs Officer.</i>

42
00:05:26,985 --> 00:05:31,185
<i>For thousands of years, smugglers</i>
<i>and we have been playing hide and seek.</i>

43
00:05:31,265 --> 00:05:34,225
<i>Sometimes, they win. Sometimes us.</i>
<i>Sometimes it's a win-win.</i>

44
00:05:42,105 --> 00:05:44,105
<i>Just like every day,</i>

45
00:05:44,185 --> 00:05:47,425
<i>some smugglers have left for Mumbai</i>
<i>from across the world.</i>

46
00:05:47,505 --> 00:05:49,385
<i>Let's see who wins today.</i>

47
00:08:40,264 --> 00:08:41,625
There's a total of 50 bags.

48
00:08:43,144 --> 00:08:44,585
{\an8}Declare these three iPhones.

49
00:08:45,144 --> 00:08:47,825
The pickup will meet you at Arrivals.
Hand these over to him.

50
00:09:47,985 --> 00:09:50,585
- Hello, sir. Mikki speaking.
- Yes, Mikki.

51
00:09:50,665 --> 00:09:53,225
A one crore consignment
will land in your shift.

52
00:09:53,305 --> 00:09:56,305
Settle for any amount you want,
but I'll take 1.5 lakh.

53
00:09:56,385 --> 00:09:57,865
Agreed. Tell me the details.

54
00:09:57,945 --> 00:09:59,945
They are bringing watches on TG 317.

55
00:10:00,025 --> 00:10:03,465
- Who's bringing them?
- Hema Kangani. Seat number 14 A.

56
00:10:03,545 --> 00:10:04,745
Okay.

57
00:10:06,825 --> 00:10:09,505
- Any scope of one K?
- A lot more.

58
00:10:21,745 --> 00:10:23,345
{\an8}- Hello.
- Hi.

59
00:10:23,425 --> 00:10:25,425
Seat 8 BEF.

60
00:10:25,505 --> 00:10:26,945
Yeah, yeah. There it is.

61
00:10:27,025 --> 00:10:28,985
<i>Beta,</i> left. On your left.

62
00:10:29,065 --> 00:10:32,145
- Yeah. Here.
- This one, <i>beta.</i> This one.

63
00:10:46,945 --> 00:10:48,665
You want to sit here?

64
00:10:50,265 --> 00:10:53,505
Let's exchange. You come here. Okay?

65
00:10:58,945 --> 00:11:01,545
- Thank you.
- It's okay.

66
00:11:02,225 --> 00:11:04,705
Oh, nice. You got a window seat.

67
00:11:04,785 --> 00:11:06,465
Thank you.

68
00:11:06,545 --> 00:11:08,825
- Would you like to sit here?
- No. It's okay.

69
00:11:17,065 --> 00:11:20,185
<i>These four people are in the air</i>
<i>and they don't even know</i>

70
00:11:20,265 --> 00:11:23,585
<i>what happened in Delhi 48 hours ago.</i>

71
00:11:26,785 --> 00:11:30,985
<i>Two days ago, the opposition in Parliament</i>
<i>put the blame directly</i>

72
00:11:31,065 --> 00:11:34,185
<i>on the Finance Minister for the loss of</i>
<i>40,000 crores annually</i>

73
00:11:34,265 --> 00:11:37,225
<i>to our country due to smuggling.</i>

74
00:11:40,385 --> 00:11:41,305
<i>And then what…</i>

75
00:11:41,385 --> 00:11:43,865
Enough Avinash.
I don't think I can take anymore.

76
00:11:43,945 --> 00:11:45,345
With all due respect, sir,

77
00:11:45,425 --> 00:11:48,865
we caught 722 kilos of gold
in the last financial year.

78
00:11:48,945 --> 00:11:53,065
Every year, 300 tons of gold is coming
into our country through the airports.

79
00:11:53,145 --> 00:11:55,345
And you caught only 722 kilos?

80
00:11:55,425 --> 00:11:57,665
As Chairman, Customs,
is this not your failure?

81
00:11:58,225 --> 00:12:02,345
Sir, please compare our customs
intelligence budget with other countries.

82
00:12:03,065 --> 00:12:05,985
It's 100 crore.
Sir, what can be done in 100 crore?

83
00:12:06,065 --> 00:12:10,825
Yes, we do have a reward system
like other countries. But how much?

84
00:12:10,905 --> 00:12:13,705
Sir, a customs officer
cannot claim a reward

85
00:12:13,785 --> 00:12:16,225
of more than 20 lakhs
in their entire career.

86
00:12:16,305 --> 00:12:20,985
Many times, that too takes five years
to be disbursed. There's so much red tape.

87
00:12:21,065 --> 00:12:24,985
Please think, for a person running
a 60,000 crore smuggling racket,

88
00:12:25,065 --> 00:12:28,505
it's not a big deal to disburse
200 crore rupees to our officers.

89
00:12:28,585 --> 00:12:30,865
So you are saying,
your officers are corrupt?

90
00:12:31,625 --> 00:12:34,985
If that's the case,
what is your vigilance department doing?

91
00:12:35,545 --> 00:12:38,825
How many officers were caught
red-handed and action taken against them?

92
00:12:39,465 --> 00:12:43,265
Sir, corruption is present not only
among low ranks. Everyone is involved.

93
00:12:43,345 --> 00:12:45,625
- Now, our system is such--
- Avinash!

94
00:12:45,705 --> 00:12:47,145
I want a crack-down on this.

95
00:12:47,945 --> 00:12:50,945
The media is knocking at our doors.
And elections are coming.

96
00:12:51,025 --> 00:12:52,225
Prepare a list.

97
00:12:52,945 --> 00:12:56,505
It should have some honest,
motivated and hungry officers.

98
00:12:57,145 --> 00:12:58,305
These are rare species.

99
00:12:59,025 --> 00:13:00,065
What did you say?

100
00:13:00,145 --> 00:13:03,865
Sir, the officers who are honest,
motivated and hungry

101
00:13:03,945 --> 00:13:05,065
are rare species.

102
00:13:05,665 --> 00:13:07,665
In fact, they are
on the brink of extinction.

103
00:13:08,825 --> 00:13:10,425
I'll need time to find them.

104
00:13:10,505 --> 00:13:13,545
Forty-eight hours, Avinash.
That's all you have.

105
00:13:14,265 --> 00:13:15,225
Sir.

106
00:13:17,065 --> 00:13:19,465
Prepare a list of top officers. Right now.

107
00:13:20,905 --> 00:13:23,265
<i>A very intelligent man had said that</i>

108
00:13:23,345 --> 00:13:27,425
<i>India has elections on a regular basis,</i>
<i>that's why it somewhat keeps progressing.</i>

109
00:13:27,945 --> 00:13:29,505
<i>When you get orders from Delhi,</i>

110
00:13:29,585 --> 00:13:32,825
<i>the government employees</i>
<i>redefine efficiency.</i>

111
00:13:32,905 --> 00:13:34,385
<i>A list was made.</i>

112
00:13:34,465 --> 00:13:35,745
<i>And throughout the country…</i>

113
00:13:35,865 --> 00:13:38,585
<i>…young, hungry and motivated officers…</i>

114
00:13:38,705 --> 00:13:42,385
<i>…got posted on strategic</i>
<i>and important airports overnight.</i>

115
00:13:43,305 --> 00:13:45,305
And Assistant Commissioner Prakash Kumar

116
00:13:45,385 --> 00:13:48,825
{\an8}<i>was posted</i>
<i>at the Mumbai International Airport.</i>

117
00:13:52,785 --> 00:13:56,065
<i>And from that day,</i>
<i>nothing remained the same.</i>

118
00:14:21,625 --> 00:14:23,025
She has arrived.

119
00:14:42,465 --> 00:14:45,025
- Hi.
- Shalini <i>ji.</i>

120
00:14:45,105 --> 00:14:46,745
What are you declaring today?

121
00:14:48,665 --> 00:14:50,545
Just these three iPhones.

122
00:14:51,905 --> 00:14:53,065
Okay.

123
00:14:54,825 --> 00:14:56,665
- These are new models, right?
- Yes.

124
00:14:57,985 --> 00:15:00,345
Your commission will reach
your home by evening.

125
00:15:05,625 --> 00:15:09,105
Deposit 120,000 there and get
an acknowledgement on this receipt.

126
00:15:09,185 --> 00:15:11,145
And get that bag scanned.

127
00:15:53,865 --> 00:15:55,705
Okay. Your passport.

128
00:15:56,785 --> 00:15:57,945
Have a good day.

129
00:16:14,665 --> 00:16:16,945
Yes. Excuse me.

130
00:16:17,025 --> 00:16:18,705
Madam, please stop.

131
00:16:20,465 --> 00:16:22,225
- What is it, sir?
- You may go.

132
00:16:23,345 --> 00:16:24,665
- You guys--
- It's nothing.

133
00:16:24,745 --> 00:16:26,025
- Bye.
- Bye.

134
00:16:28,545 --> 00:16:30,385
Madam, please come with me.

135
00:16:31,145 --> 00:16:32,505
Yeah, please.

136
00:16:43,145 --> 00:16:45,105
Madam, you've got
three watches in the bag?

137
00:16:45,185 --> 00:16:48,505
Yes, they are for my grandchildren.

138
00:16:48,585 --> 00:16:51,905
I mean, they are gifts. The cheap ones.

139
00:16:51,985 --> 00:16:53,305
Can you show them, please?

140
00:16:54,545 --> 00:16:56,105
Raju, put the bag on the table.

141
00:17:30,505 --> 00:17:31,625
Receipt.

142
00:17:50,705 --> 00:17:52,025
Nothing else?

143
00:18:01,025 --> 00:18:02,145
You may go.

144
00:18:08,305 --> 00:18:11,745
<i>It is said that if these smugglers</i>
<i>put their mind to good use,</i>

145
00:18:11,825 --> 00:18:15,225
<i>they can solve world hunger.</i>

146
00:18:15,945 --> 00:18:19,305
<i>But they can't put their mind to good use.</i>

147
00:18:27,945 --> 00:18:29,185
Namaste, madam.

148
00:18:39,625 --> 00:18:40,945
Please come.

149
00:18:42,505 --> 00:18:43,465
- Hi!
- Hi.

150
00:18:45,025 --> 00:18:48,345
- Yes, Bangkok was very interesting.
- Hey! What are you watching?

151
00:19:17,985 --> 00:19:19,465
Thank you, madam.

152
00:19:26,825 --> 00:19:28,425
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

153
00:19:34,585 --> 00:19:35,545
Sir.

154
00:19:40,705 --> 00:19:42,305
- Sir.
- A.C. Prakash Kumar.

155
00:19:42,385 --> 00:19:44,625
- Please have a seat.
- That's okay.

156
00:20:11,025 --> 00:20:12,705
What is it? Why did you pull over?

157
00:20:13,545 --> 00:20:15,465
The engine is making some noise.

158
00:20:20,425 --> 00:20:22,745
Inside, inside. Inside.

159
00:20:24,305 --> 00:20:25,465
Move.

160
00:20:26,225 --> 00:20:27,625
Shut up!

161
00:20:30,665 --> 00:20:32,145
Keep quiet!

162
00:20:53,345 --> 00:20:54,225
Tell me.

163
00:20:54,305 --> 00:20:57,545
We have your courier, Swati Salunkhe.

164
00:20:58,385 --> 00:21:01,785
Our demand is 50 lakhs in US dollars.

165
00:21:05,865 --> 00:21:09,305
Twenty-five lakhs.
Final offer. Share the location.

166
00:21:09,385 --> 00:21:10,865
We'll inform you in one hour.

167
00:21:14,385 --> 00:21:15,705
Raghu!

168
00:21:20,945 --> 00:21:22,385
I have a job for you.

169
00:21:35,545 --> 00:21:37,745
A.C. Prakash Kumar
reporting for duty, sir.

170
00:21:45,305 --> 00:21:46,865
Your joining date is tomorrow, right?

171
00:21:47,465 --> 00:21:49,185
Sir, I reached Mumbai last night.

172
00:21:49,265 --> 00:21:51,825
I thought to check the airport
instead of wasting time.

173
00:21:54,585 --> 00:21:58,785
A person like you is called
enthu cutlet in local slang.

174
00:21:59,665 --> 00:22:01,065
Walk with me.

175
00:22:03,425 --> 00:22:04,705
Sir!

176
00:22:04,785 --> 00:22:06,385
Sir, I made a detailed report

177
00:22:06,465 --> 00:22:08,145
on how to curb smuggling in this airport.

178
00:22:08,225 --> 00:22:11,985
Firstly, we have to randomly change
the officers sitting in accounts shift.

179
00:22:12,065 --> 00:22:13,625
This will ensure a--

180
00:22:13,705 --> 00:22:15,305
- Put it in the car.
- Sir.

181
00:22:16,105 --> 00:22:16,945
This will--

182
00:22:17,025 --> 00:22:20,505
You think that my officers
are in collusion with the smugglers.

183
00:22:21,425 --> 00:22:22,425
I don't know, sir.

184
00:22:22,505 --> 00:22:26,505
You want to say that my officers
are corrupt, incompetent?

185
00:22:29,705 --> 00:22:32,625
- Excuse me.
- Yes, sir?

186
00:22:32,705 --> 00:22:34,105
Where are you coming from?

187
00:22:34,825 --> 00:22:36,105
From Al Dera, sir.

188
00:22:37,225 --> 00:22:39,825
- Any problem, sir?
- No problem. Just routine.

189
00:22:40,745 --> 00:22:41,945
Let's check your bag.

190
00:22:42,585 --> 00:22:44,105
Sir, it's a medical emergency.

191
00:22:44,625 --> 00:22:46,785
I've to reach Pune.
My father is very critical.

192
00:22:46,865 --> 00:22:49,465
- It'll take two minutes. Come.
- I'm already late. Sir, please.

193
00:22:49,545 --> 00:22:50,505
Put your bag in there.

194
00:22:55,225 --> 00:22:57,465
- Sir.
- Laptop bag.

195
00:22:58,545 --> 00:23:01,905
- Sir, there's nothing in it, just laptop.
- I know it's a laptop. Put it.

196
00:23:09,585 --> 00:23:10,705
Forward.

197
00:23:12,345 --> 00:23:13,785
Pull back a little.

198
00:23:21,145 --> 00:23:22,745
- Open it.
- Sir, sir.

199
00:23:24,505 --> 00:23:26,225
Sir. Sir, sir.

200
00:23:26,305 --> 00:23:28,705
It has very important data, sir.
It can crash.

201
00:23:28,785 --> 00:23:30,145
Your data will be safe.

202
00:23:30,225 --> 00:23:32,625
Sir, please stop.
I'll come with backup tomorrow.

203
00:23:32,705 --> 00:23:33,905
- Then you can--
- Relax.

204
00:23:33,985 --> 00:23:35,465
Sir, please, try to understand.

205
00:23:35,545 --> 00:23:37,145
Just two minutes, my dear.

206
00:23:37,225 --> 00:23:39,145
The screen will break. Please flip it.

207
00:23:39,225 --> 00:23:40,425
Don't make a mess and keep quiet.

208
00:23:52,425 --> 00:23:55,225
Sir, this is not mine. I swear by my mom.

209
00:23:55,945 --> 00:23:59,265
Sir, the lady sitting besides me
had a brown bag. I think it got exchanged.

210
00:23:59,345 --> 00:24:00,785
Sir, I…

211
00:24:02,265 --> 00:24:04,345
Sir, I didn't do this. My dad's sick…

212
00:24:13,465 --> 00:24:14,585
It was a good stunt.

213
00:24:15,265 --> 00:24:16,345
Thank you, sir.

214
00:24:16,425 --> 00:24:19,825
Sir, if you permit me
to post 30 new officers here,

215
00:24:19,905 --> 00:24:21,505
I can raise a new team here.

216
00:24:24,105 --> 00:24:28,065
Prakash, I know that you were
handpicked by the Finance Minister.

217
00:24:29,065 --> 00:24:30,865
But you need to know

218
00:24:30,945 --> 00:24:33,785
that I cannot transfer 30 officers
without a reason.

219
00:24:37,185 --> 00:24:38,345
Hello, sir.

220
00:24:39,665 --> 00:24:42,545
No problem, sir. Sure, sir, sure.

221
00:24:44,065 --> 00:24:45,745
Welcome, sir. Welcome.

222
00:24:46,305 --> 00:24:49,865
So, here comes
your first official assignment.

223
00:24:50,945 --> 00:24:53,665
Mr. Siddharth Gupta is coming
on the Singapore flight today.

224
00:24:54,265 --> 00:24:55,745
Take care of his protocol.

225
00:25:05,345 --> 00:25:10,665
<i>Taking care of the protocol means</i>
<i>making a VIP feel like a VVIP.</i>

226
00:25:10,745 --> 00:25:11,665
Please come, sir.

227
00:25:26,545 --> 00:25:29,985
<i>Prakash sir was given the task</i>
<i>of taking care of the protocol</i>

228
00:25:30,065 --> 00:25:33,865
<i>for Siddharth Gupta,</i>
<i>the only son-in-law of a politician.</i>

229
00:25:57,905 --> 00:25:59,865
- Excuse me.
- Yes, sir?

230
00:25:59,945 --> 00:26:02,425
- May I get one more?
- Sure, sir.

231
00:26:19,025 --> 00:26:22,745
<i>Prakash sir was not only young</i>
<i>and dedicated, but intelligent too.</i>

232
00:26:22,865 --> 00:26:24,825
<i>He very well knew the result</i>

233
00:26:24,905 --> 00:26:28,065
<i>of not giving the son-in-law</i>
<i>a proper welcome.</i>

234
00:26:28,145 --> 00:26:31,105
<i>Prakash sir gave the son-in-law</i>
<i>such a welcome</i>

235
00:26:31,185 --> 00:26:33,665
<i>that the son-in-law and officers</i>

236
00:26:33,745 --> 00:26:36,225
<i>at Mumbai airport</i>
<i>will remember that welcome for years.</i>

237
00:26:37,745 --> 00:26:41,865
Excuse me. May I? Thank you.

238
00:26:45,225 --> 00:26:46,265
Good afternoon, sir.

239
00:26:46,345 --> 00:26:48,585
Nobody came to receive me at the airport.

240
00:26:48,665 --> 00:26:50,385
Did you not inform anybody?

241
00:26:50,465 --> 00:26:52,225
Sir, I talked to the commissioner myself.

242
00:26:52,305 --> 00:26:53,905
<i>- Give me two minutes, sir.</i>
- Bloody hell!

243
00:26:55,305 --> 00:26:58,185
Excuse me?
Why not just stroll in the garden?

244
00:27:25,625 --> 00:27:26,865
Excuse me.

245
00:28:00,305 --> 00:28:02,785
Zoom in Cam 14 on the hand.

246
00:28:31,545 --> 00:28:34,625
- Thapa?
<i>- Jai Hind,</i> sir.

247
00:28:34,705 --> 00:28:36,665
<i>Jai Hind.</i> How are you?

248
00:28:36,745 --> 00:28:38,745
- Are you fine?
- Absolutely fine, sir.

249
00:28:39,785 --> 00:28:41,225
When did you join here?

250
00:28:41,305 --> 00:28:43,545
Did you take charge today?

251
00:28:44,065 --> 00:28:45,705
What to say, Thapa?

252
00:28:46,505 --> 00:28:48,665
You have got your network here also.

253
00:28:48,745 --> 00:28:50,145
Yes, sir.

254
00:28:52,905 --> 00:28:54,145
Thapa, tell me something.

255
00:29:02,905 --> 00:29:06,505
Pawar sir.
Pawar sir is the best man for this.

256
00:29:07,185 --> 00:29:10,785
Just a while back
a punter made a fool of Pawar sir.

257
00:29:11,385 --> 00:29:13,345
Pawar sir is in a bad mood.

258
00:29:48,105 --> 00:29:50,945
Excuse me. Excuse me.

259
00:29:51,025 --> 00:29:53,505
- On the line…
- As it starts, the traffic is stuck.

260
00:29:54,025 --> 00:29:55,625
Excuse me. AIU.

261
00:29:55,705 --> 00:29:56,705
What is it?

262
00:29:56,785 --> 00:29:59,585
You came through green channel.
Is there nothing to declare?

263
00:30:01,385 --> 00:30:03,905
- What's your name, Officer?
- Aabhas Pawar.

264
00:30:03,985 --> 00:30:05,465
Why do you want to know?

265
00:30:07,665 --> 00:30:09,225
My name is Siddharth Gupta.

266
00:30:09,305 --> 00:30:10,985
And I have nothing to declare.

267
00:30:11,065 --> 00:30:13,225
So you are wearing a fake Piaget?

268
00:30:15,665 --> 00:30:19,385
I bought it in Mumbai.
And I was wearing it when I left.

269
00:30:19,465 --> 00:30:22,145
Who sold it to you in Mumbai?

270
00:30:25,065 --> 00:30:27,545
Smart. Very smart.

271
00:30:30,625 --> 00:30:31,745
Do one thing, Pawar.

272
00:30:32,545 --> 00:30:34,265
Send someone with me outside.

273
00:30:34,345 --> 00:30:35,945
I'll give you two lakh rupees.

274
00:30:36,545 --> 00:30:38,545
For your snacks. Happy?

275
00:30:38,625 --> 00:30:40,465
Come with me.

276
00:30:40,545 --> 00:30:42,305
Pawar, I said it is not needed.

277
00:30:42,385 --> 00:30:43,905
- Send someone out--
- Come with me.

278
00:30:43,985 --> 00:30:46,385
- Pawar. Don't touch me. Where to?
- Come with me.

279
00:30:46,465 --> 00:30:48,505
- Where are you taking me? Leave my bag.
- Yeah.

280
00:30:48,585 --> 00:30:49,945
- Don't touch me. Okay?
- Come on.

281
00:30:50,025 --> 00:30:51,505
Where are you taking me?

282
00:30:51,585 --> 00:30:53,505
Come with me inside. Come on.

283
00:30:53,585 --> 00:30:55,985
- Come on.
- Let me see where you're taking me.

284
00:30:56,065 --> 00:30:58,145
- Don't touch me. I'm telling you.
- Come.

285
00:30:58,225 --> 00:31:01,585
- Where to? Tell me. Left, right? Where?
- Right.

286
00:31:02,305 --> 00:31:03,185
Come in, sir.

287
00:31:10,945 --> 00:31:15,745
You're giving me snack-money after saving
1.5 crore duty on a five crore watch?

288
00:31:16,345 --> 00:31:17,665
You think, I'm a beggar?

289
00:31:18,425 --> 00:31:20,425
- Listen.
- Take off your clothes.

290
00:31:20,505 --> 00:31:23,185
Take off your clothes for strip search.

291
00:31:23,945 --> 00:31:24,865
Come on.

292
00:31:26,425 --> 00:31:28,785
Remember, there is no CCTV here.

293
00:31:28,865 --> 00:31:31,385
I will give you a good thrashing.

294
00:31:32,145 --> 00:31:33,705
Take off the clothes, mother--

295
00:31:34,225 --> 00:31:35,425
Take them off.

296
00:31:39,745 --> 00:31:41,065
Who are you calling?

297
00:31:46,585 --> 00:31:48,185
Pawar, have you gone nuts?

298
00:31:49,265 --> 00:31:50,145
Sir…

299
00:31:51,305 --> 00:31:54,145
I didn't know
that he's Mr. Bhonsle's son-in-law.

300
00:31:54,905 --> 00:31:57,345
Sir, why are we all being punished
for his fault?

301
00:31:57,425 --> 00:32:00,865
- Why are we being transferred?
- Because you all were there with him.

302
00:32:01,465 --> 00:32:03,025
It's the style of the powerful.

303
00:32:03,105 --> 00:32:06,865
Now, no customs officer
will stop his son-in-law for ten years.

304
00:32:06,945 --> 00:32:08,225
Sir, please do something.

305
00:32:08,785 --> 00:32:11,705
My wife can't bear
the cold weather of Nathu La.

306
00:32:11,785 --> 00:32:14,505
Sorry, my hands are tied.
I got a call from the Ministry.

307
00:32:14,585 --> 00:32:18,185
Complete all your exit formalities
before the end of the shift.

308
00:32:18,265 --> 00:32:19,305
Sir, please.

309
00:32:27,065 --> 00:32:29,825
I told you to lead the protocol, Prakash.

310
00:32:29,905 --> 00:32:31,665
I gave you a simple task.

311
00:32:31,745 --> 00:32:33,745
I had to leave my granddaughter's party.

312
00:32:33,825 --> 00:32:36,025
As my joining date was tomorrow,
so the system

313
00:32:36,105 --> 00:32:38,625
did not generate
my I-Card and all access key-card.

314
00:32:38,705 --> 00:32:41,585
You were in a hurry this morning,
so I didn't even get your number.

315
00:32:41,665 --> 00:32:43,345
I didn't know anybody here.

316
00:32:43,425 --> 00:32:44,865
So I was quite helpless.

317
00:32:44,945 --> 00:32:47,825
By the time I got your number,
it was all over, sir.

318
00:32:52,945 --> 00:32:54,345
This Pawar is an idiot.

319
00:32:55,065 --> 00:32:56,385
Why did he have to do that?

320
00:32:56,465 --> 00:32:59,185
- We are already short-staffed--
- Sir, this is a list.

321
00:32:59,265 --> 00:33:01,585
Please revoke the suspension
of three officers.

322
00:33:01,665 --> 00:33:03,665
These three will make a team themselves.

323
00:33:09,345 --> 00:33:11,905
Arjun Meena,
Ravinder Gujjar, Mitali Kamat.

324
00:33:12,505 --> 00:33:14,465
- Right, sir.
- Do you know them?

325
00:33:14,545 --> 00:33:17,065
I don't know them personally,
but I do know about them.

326
00:33:27,265 --> 00:33:28,945
<i>- Yes, sir?</i>
- Send Sawant inside.

327
00:33:42,065 --> 00:33:42,905
What's up?

328
00:34:27,025 --> 00:34:28,585
You wanna eat banana?

329
00:34:36,065 --> 00:34:37,505
Go!

330
00:34:42,865 --> 00:34:43,824
Let's go!

331
00:34:43,905 --> 00:34:44,744
Moving out!

332
00:34:48,744 --> 00:34:49,824
Let's move, let's move.

333
00:34:55,945 --> 00:34:56,784
Raghu!

334
00:34:57,905 --> 00:35:00,505
- Swati, are you okay?
- I won't spare that bastard.

335
00:35:02,785 --> 00:35:03,825
He ran that way.

336
00:35:13,305 --> 00:35:16,425
Swati, what are you doing?
Don't run or you'll be in trouble.

337
00:35:20,305 --> 00:35:21,145
Hey!

338
00:35:22,305 --> 00:35:23,305
Hey! Stop!

339
00:35:31,785 --> 00:35:34,945
Where are you running off to? You mother…

340
00:35:36,145 --> 00:35:39,465
Leave me! Leave me, woman!

341
00:35:39,545 --> 00:35:40,545
Bloody…

342
00:36:04,105 --> 00:36:05,065
Stop!

343
00:36:07,185 --> 00:36:08,585
I will kill you if you don't move.

344
00:36:08,665 --> 00:36:10,025
Move it! Move it!

345
00:36:10,105 --> 00:36:11,505
Start the engine.

346
00:36:12,745 --> 00:36:15,185
Move, move. Let's go. Let's go.

347
00:36:16,465 --> 00:36:17,825
Let's go. Let's go.

348
00:36:21,585 --> 00:36:24,385
<i>The drugs that Swati Salunkhe</i>
<i>was bringing from Ethiopia,</i>

349
00:36:24,465 --> 00:36:27,585
<i>I got a tip off about that</i>
<i>from an intelligence officer there.</i>

350
00:36:27,665 --> 00:36:30,185
<i>And I forwarded the same tip off</i>
<i>to Moosa and Tony.</i>

351
00:36:43,665 --> 00:36:44,625
Water?

352
00:36:45,825 --> 00:36:47,265
Madam, have some water.

353
00:36:48,145 --> 00:36:51,185
You ran so much.
Why don't you want some water, Swati?

354
00:36:58,905 --> 00:37:01,425
Your system will get upset. Come on.

355
00:37:01,505 --> 00:37:03,545
Hey! Let go of my hand!

356
00:37:03,625 --> 00:37:06,705
<i>Ramesh bhai, if you want the girl,</i>
<i>you have to pay 50 lakhs.</i>

357
00:37:06,785 --> 00:37:09,465
<i>Send someone to the helipad.</i>
<i>I'll be there in an hour.</i>

358
00:38:14,505 --> 00:38:16,145
Yes, Sawant sir. What is it?

359
00:38:16,225 --> 00:38:19,705
Superintendent Meena,
your suspension has been revoked.

360
00:38:20,545 --> 00:38:23,185
The new AC sir
wants to see you immediately.

361
00:38:24,265 --> 00:38:25,185
I'm on my way.

362
00:39:00,025 --> 00:39:03,105
Tell your boss
that my suspension has been revoked.

363
00:39:03,185 --> 00:39:06,025
None of his couriers
will cross my airport from tomorrow.

364
00:39:06,105 --> 00:39:07,385
Got it?

365
00:39:08,905 --> 00:39:11,825
If you are now being so honest,
then return this money too.

366
00:39:12,785 --> 00:39:14,705
Why are you collecting this ransom?

367
00:39:17,185 --> 00:39:18,825
Because luck does not favor you.

368
00:39:18,905 --> 00:39:22,305
I got the call to join the duty
after getting the money.

369
00:39:22,385 --> 00:39:25,665
Had it come a little earlier,
your boss could have saved the money.

370
00:39:33,345 --> 00:39:35,305
<i>I got my job back,</i>

371
00:39:35,385 --> 00:39:39,825
<i>but at that time</i>
<i>I had no clue of what lay ahead.</i>

372
00:43:56,265 --> 00:44:01,265
Subtitle translation by: Sanjay Malhotra
